OL,3,CGovernment face vote on controversial
OL,4,Ctwo-child benefit cap
OL,6,FMPs will vote later on an amendment
OL,7,Fcalling for the two-child cap on Child
OL,8,FBenefit to be scrapped- our Political
OL,9,FReporter Jasmine Cameron Chileshe
OL,10,Fexplains
OL,12,FThe new Labour government is facing
OL,13,Fthe threat of its first backbench
OL,14,Frevolt, as MPs prepare to vote on the
OL,15,Fcontroversial two-child benefit cap.
OL,17,FKeir Starmer has been under mounting
OL,18,Fpressure to scrap the policy, which
OL,19,Frestricts child welfare payments to
OL,20,Fthe first two children born in most
OL,21,Ffamilies with some exceptions.
