OL,6,FThe prime minister and his cabinet say
OL,7,Fthe state of the public finances means
OL,8,Fthey cannot afford to abolish the
OL,9,Fbenefit limit without economic growth.
OL,11,FThe cap affects some 1.6 million
OL,12,Fchildren, and as child poverty rates
OL,13,Frise, the PM has faced calls from
OL,14,Fcharities, opposition parties and some
OL,15,Fof his own backbench MPs to scrap the
OL,16,Flimit.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
