OL,6,FHe urged the government to take action
OL,7,Fand scrap the cap: "The costs of
OL,8,Fhaving children grow up in poverty
OL,9,Foutweigh the costs of lifting them out
OL,10,Fof poverty", he said.
OL,12,FSNP Westminster leader Stephen Flynn
OL,13,Furged Scottish Labour MPs to back the
OL,14,Fparty's amendment to remove the cap.
OL,16,F"Keir Starmer must not fail his first
OL,17,Fmajor test in Government by refusing
OL,18,Fto scrap the cap," he said.
