OL,6,F"I'll be voting for the SNP amendment.
OL,7,FI don't like voting for other parties'
OL,8,Famendments but but I'm following Keir
OL,9,FStarmer's example as he said put
OL,10,Fcountry before party. So I'm putting
OL,11,Flifting children out of poverty before
OL,12,Fparty whipping or anything like that."
OL,14,FKim Johnson and Rosie Duffield are
OL,15,Falso among the Labour MPs who have
OL,16,Furged Starmer to change tack, while
OL,17,FConservative Suella Braverman spoke on
OL,18,FMonday to support scrapping the limit.
